@logic-eval text
Use logic-eval when a plan needs a bounded reasoning-orchestration helper, not when it needs the final solved answer directly.
logic-eval should read a logic-heavy request, produce a structured rewrite brief, recommend one or more external reasoning interpreters, and preserve the exact entities, constraints, answer requirements, and downstream routing cues for the next step.
Prefer direct HumanLikeReasoner routing when the planner already understands that the task is a bounded human-scale reasoning problem. Prefer direct AdvancedReasoner routing when the task is already clearly uncertain, evidential, probabilistic, causal, argumentative, legal, scientific, optimization-oriented, formal-routing, pragmatic, analogical, ethical, or creative in the bounded meta-reasoning sense. Use logic-eval when the planner needs help rewriting or decomposing the request before handing it to an external reasoning interpreter.
Do not use logic-eval as the synthesis surface for document-scale Markdown or JSON workflows. Those belong in DocumentScalePlanner when explicit chunking and rollups are required.
Avoid logic-eval for final prose, memo writing, arbitrary scripting, document-plan synthesis, or as a duplicate solver runtime. The output should be a machine-usable orchestration brief, not the final user-facing answer.
